A new repository can be initiated using the command line, RStudio, or GitHub. However, this document will specifically describe the process using GitHub, as it facilitates compliance with the reproducible research SOP.

Once employees become PhEpiGit members, they have write permissions, allowing them to clone, pull, and push to all PhEpiGit repositories.

PhEpiGit provides a **project_template** repository that should be used each time a member creates a new repository. This template includes all the folders indicated in PhEpi-1-05_Reproduzierbares Arbeiten.

1. Go to the upper-right corner of the PhEpiGit and select +, among the options select **New repository**

![Create a new repository](images/newrepo.png){#fig-newrepo .absolute top=160 left=380 width="700"}

<!-- this is the rectangle -->

:::{style="position: absolute; left: 490px; top: 395px; height: 35px; width: 245px; border:2px solid #004a6f; padding: 0px; padding-left: 0px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 0px #85929e; border-radius: 5px;"}
:::




2. Select the **Pharmacoepidemiology-UHHD/project_template** (see xxx) to create the new repository (A). This automatically will select the PhEpi as owner. Name the repository (B) and choose a repository visibility (C). Additionally you can add a description. Lastly, click **Create repositry**



![Create a new repository window](images/newrepo2.png){#fig-newrepo2 .absolute top=160 left=380 width="700"}

<!-- this is the circle -->

:::{style="position: absolute; left: 365px; top: 945px; height: 35px; width: 35px; border:0px solid #004aad; padding: 0px; padding-left: 0px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 0px #85929e; border-radius: 5px;"}
<div class="numberCircle">A</div>
:::


:::{style="position: absolute; left: 365px; top: 1190px; height: 35px; width: 35px; border:0px solid #004aad; padding: 0px; padding-left: 0px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 0px #85929e; border-radius: 5px;"}
<div class="numberCircle">B</div>
:::


:::{style="position: absolute; left: 365px; top: 1280px; height: 35px; width: 35px; border:0px solid #004aad; padding: 0px; padding-left: 0px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px 0px #85929e; border-radius: 5px;"}
<div class="numberCircle">C</div>
:::

@fig-newrepo3  shows a walkthrough of how a new repository takes shape. While GitHub enables repository management tasks, complete control can be achieved using a command line text editor or tools such as RStudio. This SOP emphasizes utilizing RStudio as a central element for effective GitHub repository management.

![New repository content based on PhEpi-1-05_Reproduzierbares Arbeiten](images/newrepo3.png){#fig-newrepo3 .absolute top=160 left=380 width="500"}

